ARTICLE.TITLE: The Killers share 'Dying Breed' | Gigwise
ARTICLE.TEXT:
New album Imploding The Mirage is out next week

The Killers continue to walk the path towards a new kind of Fleetwood Mac-inspired pop with a brand new single 'Dying Breed'. It's the last taste of Imploding The Mirage, which arrives next week.

Kicking off like it's a Crack Cloud tune, The Killers soon move into some big boy heartland rock by way of proper rock drum breakdown. Drama, drama, drama! Imploding The Mirage looks set to be a real corker for the heatwave, what with three juicy singles already out in the open.

The Killers first unveiled plans for their new album back in March with the soaring 'Caution' - a summertime banger charged with a proper Lindsey Buckingham riff. Since then, they've also shared 'My Own Soul's Warning'.

See all the rescheduled dates for the live UK and Ireland Tour - now slap-bang in the middle of summer 2021. They'll see support from Sam Fender, Manic Street Preachers and Blossoms.
